   ```html
   <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/qrcodejs/1.0.0/qrcode.min.js"></script>
   ```

2. Create a canvas element in your HTML where the QR code will be displayed:
   ```html
   <canvas id="qrcode"></canvas>
   ```

3. Add the following JavaScript code to your file to generate the QR code:
   ```javascript
   // Create a new QRCode object
   var qrcode = new QRCode(document.getElementById('qrcode'));

   // Generate the QR code for the URL
   qrcode.makeCode('www.google.com');
   ```

Make sure the HTML and JavaScript code are included in the same file or in the correct order if they are in separate files. When you run your code, the QR code for `www.google.com` will be generated and displayed on the canvas element with the id `qrcode`.

